overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by adding a database for response storage, an admin dashboard for
  data access, and an authentication system. The core intent was to fulfill the
  requirements outlined in a provided Statement of Work. The approach involved
  updating the application's demographics fields to align with the SOW,
  designing a Prisma schema for  to store detailed
  questionnaire data, and developing a suite of API endpoints for data
  submission, retrieval, and CSV export. A key decision was to implement a
  simple password-based authentication system for the admin dashboard, which was
  later refined to leverage Next.js middleware for cleaner route protection. The
  implementation included creating dedicated admin login and dashboard pages.
  Extensive testing confirmed that all database operations, API routes,
  authentication, and CSV export functionalities were working as expected,
  providing a robust solution for the client.
